            <P><font face="Arial" size="2"><a name="newdisc"></a><b><font color="#ff0000">Help Needed With Copy Protection</font></b></font>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">From: "<a href="mailto:capb@integrated-learning.com">Catherine
            Parvensky Barwell</a>"</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">I have been having a problem with
            people copying one of my websites ( <a href="http://www.grocerybiz.info">www.grocerybiz.info</a>
            ). In one case, the individual actually stole the entire 100+ page
            site, downloaded it into a database and was prepared to sell
            replicated sites to others. I have the site right click protected,
            but this does not prevent someone from selecting "save as"
            from the file menu, nor does it prevent someone from saving pages
            from Adobe Acrobat (which has also happened). I have taken
            appropriate action against the copyright infringers, but I would
            like to prevent this from happening yet again in the future.</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">Does anyone know how to adequately
            protect an entire site from being copied?</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">Any help would be greatly
            appreciated.</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">Sincerely,</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">Catherine Barwell<br>
            President<br>
            Integrated Learning Technology, Inc.<br>
            <a href="http://www.integrated-learning.com">www.integrated-learning.com</a>&nbsp;<br>
            </font></p>
