            <P><b><font color="#ff0000" face="Arial" size="2">Browser Compatibility -- How Far Do You Go?</font></b>

            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">From: <a href="mailto:allan@associateprograms.com">Allan
            Gardyne</a></font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">I've just redesigned my main page
            after leaving the design more or less untouched for years, and
            really need some advice.</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">I checked the new design with the
            free trial tool at <a href="http://www.netmechanic.com">http://www.netmechanic.com</a>&nbsp;
            and viewed it through Netscape and Internet Explorer browsers and it
            looks OK.</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">However, it looks jolly awful when
            viewed through the free tool at <a href="http://www.anybrowser.com">http://www.anybrowser.com</a>
            .&nbsp;</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">Is that something I need to worry
            about?</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">All the best from Down Under.</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">Allan Gardyne&nbsp;<a href="http://www.AssociatePrograms.com"><br>
            http://www.AssociatePrograms.com</a>&nbsp;</font></p>

            <P>
            <a href="mailto:design@adventive.com">
            <FONT face=Arial size=2>
