            <hr>

            <P><b><font color="#ff0000" face="Arial" size="2">Browser Compatibility -- How Far Do You Go?</font></b>

            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">From: <a href="mailto:craigbutler@northwesternmutual.com">Craig
            Butler</a></font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">I am looking to see if anyone is
            aware of a good resource that has documented a comparison of
            browser/operating system platforms compatibility? As our sites
            require coverage for a broad customer base and the fact that we
            still see Netscape and I.E. 4 browsers being used by a significant
            number of our visitors, I am trying to determine just how much I can
            scale back on our testing efforts.</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">An example of questions I would like
            get answers to are: 1) if we need to support Netscape 4x would 4.78
            provide enough coverage so that I don't need to test 4.72 and 4.76?</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">2) is there a enough of a difference
            between I.E. 5.0 and I.E. 5.01 and even I.E. 5.5 that warrants
            testing two or three of these or would testing one be effective
            enough?</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">3) from the various windows based
            operating systems, can we discard testing one version over another?</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">I am sure anyone who has worked on
            this issue in the past has had the same questions and I was hoping
            someone would have documented this for the benefit of those
            individuals who find themselves stuck in testing labs across the
            country.</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">Regards,<br>
            <br>
            Craig Butler<br>
            Internet Application Support<br>
            Northwestern Mutual</font></p>

            <P>
            <a href="mailto:design@adventive.com">
