            <hr>

            <P>

            <b><font size="2"><a name="contidisc5"><font face="arial" color="#ff0000"></font></a><font face="arial" color="#ff0000"><br>
            Mandatory Alt Attributes On IMG Tags</font></font></b>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">From: "<a href="mailto:dmwrite@cybertrails.com">Don
            Miller</a>"</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">One problem with the ALT tag is that
            new browsers (Mozilla, Netscape 7) look for the TITLE tag. IE
            appears to read either one but if the TITLE tag is present, it will
            skip the ALT. NS 4.x looks for the ALT tag. I would recommend using
            both tags on all images and the TITLE tag on all text links.</font></p>
            <p><font face="Arial" size="2">Don G. Miller<br>
            Freelance Technical Writer<br>
            Web Designer<br>
            <a href="http://www.dgmservices.com">http://www.dgmservices.com</a>&nbsp;</font></p>

            <P>
            <a href="mailto:design@adventive.com">
            <FONT face=Arial size=2>
            <img border="0" src="http://www.audettemedia.com/emailtest/images/comment.gif" width="130" height="20">
            </FONT>
            </a>
            <P align=right><a href="#top"><FONT face=Arial size=2><img border="0" src="http://www.adventive.com/emailtest/images/top.jpg" width="41" height="15">
            </FONT>
